definitions.definition: Any of genus Gonorynchus (also called beaked sandfishes ), long, thin ray-finned fishes (family Gonorychidae )
Any of several marine fishes that burrow into sandy seabeds

subdefinitions.definition: in Trichodontidae , a family of perch-like fish
of species Awaous tajasica , usually sand fish , a species of goby fish (family Gobiidae )
of species Malacanthus plumieri ( sand tilefish , family Malacanthidae )
of species Diplectrum formosum ( sand perch , family Serranidae )

definitions.definition: Other animals that notably burrow in sand:

subdefinitions.definition: sandfish skink ( Scincus scincus ), a land-dwelling lizard that swims in sand
a sea cucumber of species Holothuria scabra or Thelenota ananas .
